<TITLE> Hasina, Khaleda have little to celebrate </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 14 (bdnews24.com)This time last year former prime ministers Sheikh Hasina and Khaleda Zia celebrated Pahela Baishakh in freedom; this year they observed the Bangla New Year in detention with little cause for merriment. Leaders and workers of both Awami League and BNP gathered Monday morning at the Sangsad Bhaban premises, where the two former prime ministers are detained in special jails, with offerings of flowers and other gifts as New Year greetings. Sunday night, New Year's eve, saw prison authorities also offering Baishakhi flowers to Hasina and Khaleda. Deputy inspector general of prisons Maj Shamsul Haider Siddiqui delivered the floral greetings to the two detained leaders. The authorities also included the customary pantaa-ilish in Hasina's and Khaleda's New Year menus. Awami League presidium member Motia Chowdhury, acting general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam, central party leadesr Abdul Mannan and Dr Mostafa Jalal Mohiuddin, and city unit president Abdul Aziz were among those who handed flower bouquets to the jail superintendent to pass on to detained party president Hasina. BNP vice president Sarwari Rahman, joint secretary general Selima Rahman, former lawmaker Shirin Sultana, Mohila Dal leaders and BNP ward commissioners handed over flowers, fruits and books as New Year gifts for party chairperson Khaleda. bdnews24
